## HTTP API

Public request and response structs live in `api/http/model/`. Add and generate an API with:

First define `UserInfo` (and any complex request type) as a Go struct in `api/http/model/`, then run:

```bash
jgo api add GetUser --method GET --path /get_user \
  --request uid:int64:required \
  --response-data UserInfo
jgo api generate

jgo call http GetUser \
  --addr http://127.0.0.1:8080 \
  --data '{"uid":12345}'
```
{{end}}
