## gRPC API

Install the locked Buf toolchain once, add an RPC, edit its protobuf fields, and generate code:

```bash
make tools
jgo rpc add GetUser --service GreeterService
# Edit api/proto/{{.PackageName}}/v1/service.proto.
jgo rpc generate

jgo call grpc GreeterService.GetUser \
  --addr 127.0.0.1:9090 \
  --data '{}'
```

`jgo rpc generate` overwrites generated protobuf and transport files, but never overwrites an existing business service method.
Generated business methods use `<Service><RPC>` names, such as `GreeterServiceGetUser`, so mixed projects can safely use the same operation name over HTTP and gRPC.
{{end}}
